abstract: Mr. Kennedy, a scion of the political dynasty, said the Trump administration was “a rebuke of our highest American ideal — that we are all worthy.”
snippet: Mr. Kennedy, a scion of the political dynasty, said the Trump administration was “a rebuke of our highest American ideal — that we are all worthy.”
lead_paragraph: BOSTON — Without uttering the president’s name, Representative Joseph P. Kennedy III chastised the Trump administration Tuesday night for what he said was its abandonment of the fundamental values for which the nation stands.

abstract: Mr. Ferrell brought back his impression of the former president, whose favorability rating has been rising. Other sketches played on the growing impact of the #MeToo movement.

lead_paragraph: When Will Ferrell returns to host “Saturday Night Live” these days, two questions promptly come to mind: How soon is he going to play President George W. Bush? And then what will he do?

abstract: The spinoff of “RuPaul’s Drag Race” returned for its third season on Thursday.
snippet: The spinoff of “RuPaul’s Drag Race” returned for its third season on Thursday.
lead_paragraph: Hello, hello, hello! “RuPaul’s Drag Race All Stars” returned for its third season last night — thank God, or thank RuPaul, however you worship. The show, a spinoff of “RuPaul’s Drag Race,” pits runners-up and fan favorites from past seasons against each other for a second chance at glory — glory being $100,000 and a spot in the “Drag Race” Hall of Fame, parodied in a clever cold open with the two previous winners Chad Michaels and Alaska (renamed “Ofrupaul”) strolling in “Handmaid’s Tale” garb. “The ‘Drag Race’ Hall of Fame really isn’t what I thought it was going to be,” Alaska said. “You look really nice in red, though.”

abstract: When we solicited questions last month for our new publisher, A. G. Sulzberger, our readers responded in droves — to the tune of some 2,500 submissions. Here are his responses.

abstract: Gordon Edelstein made unwelcome advances and crude remarks about women, lesbians and nuns, according to current and former employees. He has been placed on leave.
snippet: Gordon Edelstein made unwelcome advances and crude remarks about women, lesbians and nuns, according to current and former employees. He has been placed on leave.
lead_paragraph: The groping began about two months after Kim Rubinstein began working at Long Wharf Theater in 2003, she said.
